                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Srinagar, May 2: A chance arrest of a youth in a stone-throwing case has possibly thwarted a terror attack in Delhi.          
	Jammu and Kashmir police, assisted by central intelligence officers, arrested Umar Zargar in Srinagar today in connection with yesterdays terror alert in Delhi. Police sources said the youth was scheduled to deliver the sophisticated explosives to his handlers for triggering the blasts in the capital.          
	A source said: He was supposed to go to Delhi between April 23 to April 27 carrying pens loaded with potassium nitrate for delivery to some unidentified men.          
	His chance arrest in the stone-throwing case on April 23 scuttled his plan, the source added.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): A Government Railway Police officer allegedly shot dead his senior for putting him on night duty, before turning the gun on himself..                  
	 New Delhi: The Jharkhand stalemate is not expected to end in a hurry. The BJP has told Hemant Soren, the leader of the JMM legislature party, that he will have to ask father Shibu Soren to put quit the chief minister and also offer a letter of support to a government led by the BJP. In the meeting that BJP president Nitin Gadkari and senior leaders had with Hemant, Ajsu chief Sudesh Mahato and Jaleshwar Mahato of the Janata Dal (United) on Saturday, the party emphasised that the JMM will have to put its house in order and secure a letter of support from each MLA. Otherwise we are not interested in doing business with them, a senior leader present at the meeting said. Hemant did not give a commitment. The BJP parliamentary board that was slated to meet on Sunday, has put off the meeting indefinitely.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A Singaporean man was arrested at Delhi airport on Sunday for allegedly trying to smuggle 7 kg of hashish. Lee Weiqi, 28, was being watched by the Narcotics Control Bureau that claims to have busted a drug racket between South East Asia and Europe.                  
	 Surat (PTI): An ONGC pipeline in Gujarat sprang a leak on Sunday. No casualty has been reported.                                                                                                                                              
